title: Tileable X to Y balancer
descriptionMarkdown:
A subsection designed for combining  the output of an ore patch into arbitrary number of outputs which are packed  regardless of the input density.

This is the right hand version, and it is for red bets.  When I get time I will create a book with right and left hand versions  for yellow red and blue belts.
If space is limited the one section entering into the first splitter can be removed to reduce the height of the BP by 1.  Either or both inputs to that splitter are equivalent.  The input splitter must prioritize the right output (left on the left hand version) for it to work properly.
